POSTSECONDARY ED. Provides for medical school students' grading. (2/3-CA7s2.1(A))
(7/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 17:3384, relative to postsecondary education institutions; to require a letter-
3 based grading scale for medical doctorate degrees; to provide for an effective date;
4 and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 17:3384 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §3384. Medical school grading scale
8 A. Beginning in the 2026-2027 academic school year, all public
9 postsecondary education institutions offering medical doctorate degrees shall
10 adopt policies ensuring that any coursework offered in their curriculum for a
11 medical degree or certificate assesses a student's performance on the
12 coursework based on the assignment of a letter grade of A, B, C, D, or F, with
13 plus or minus designations for each letter A through D, or another tiered system
14 with at least four such designations.
15 B. The Board of Regents shall enforce this Section and is hereby
16 authorized to adopt policies providing for civil penalties for violations of
17 Subsection A of this Section.
